This paper is about a neural model for text summarization, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new approach that combines extractive and compressive methods for summarization, which involves techniques from machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also involves techniques such as neural networks and reinforcement learning, which are covered by sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and optimization, which are covered by sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
